text: Bora Gulari (born October 22, 1975) is an American competitive sailor. He competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, in the mixed Nacra 17. He was US Sailor of the Year in 2009 and is a 2001 graduate of the University of Michigan's College of Engineering. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1975 births Category:Living people Category:American male sailors (sport) Category:Olympic sailors of the United States Category:Sailors at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Nacra 17 Category:US Sailor of the Year Category:University of Michigan College of Engineering alumni
